<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ulvian</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-04-21 03:35:49</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Great for a Ranger.<BR>
<BR>
At 51 I now have two of those, my damage output is INSANE.<BR>
One thing though ) Make sure to tell the warrior to taunt constantly and dont snare till mob is at half life, otherwise you will end up tanking too much for my taste. Although purchasing a Swarmcaller should solve that problem.<BR>
<BR>
What I usually do is pull with flamelick (non meele damage and small taunt now). Have the warrior run in and get the 1st shot, run up next and start meele with swarmcaller till it procs (assuming im not the main tank and there is no shaman in the group). As soon as the Swarmcaller procs I whip out the Lammies and start kicking ass.<BR>
<BR>
If I am groupped with a shaman though :) no warrior needed. I pull the mob with an arrow. Have the shaman slow as soon as it is within sight range. So by the time it has reached me its wearing a 50% slow and Lammies go to work immediately.<BR>
<BR>
To any idiots saying that a Ranger cant tank, look me up on Veeshan some time. With 873 Ac, 1717 Hp unbuffed. 923 Ac 1782 Hp with self only stackeable spike coat, call of earth and strenght of nature I can buff just as well as that joe-blow paladin, with the difference of me being able to keep Mob attention.<BR>
<BR>
Ulvian Stormweaver<BR>
51st Ranger of Veeshan<BR>
-Keepers of Life-<BR>
The fasest way to someone's heart is trough their ribcage.</font></td></tr></table>
